memberOrga:
EUFIC is supported by companies along the food chain – from seed producers, through ingredient suppliers to food manufacturers. EUFIC also receives project funding from the European Commission. EUFIC is governed by a Board of Directors, which is elected from member companies. &#xd;
&#xd;
Current EUFIC members are: Abbott Nutrition, Bunge, Cargill, Cereal Partners, Coca-Cola, Dow Seeds, DSM, Ferrero, General Mills, Mondelēz Europe, Mars, Nestlé, PepsiCo, Pinar Et, Tereos, Ülker, Unilever. &#xd;
All members subscribe to EUFIC's principles and Code of Conduct (http://www.eufic.org/en/who-we-are/funding-governance; http://www.eufic.org/images/uploads/files/EUFIC_Code_of_conduct.pdf).
